article.headline: SE Louisiana 78, Texas St. 70
article.story: HAMMOND, La. (AP) -- Southeastern Louisiana's Kevyn Green scored 20 points and grabbed 13 rebounds while the inside tandem of Joseph Polite and Patrick Sullivan went a combined 13-for-13 from the floor as the Lions pulled away from Texas State to post a 78-70 Southland Conference victory Thursday. Southeastern (9-7, 1-2 SLC) finished 27-for-46 (58.7 percent) from the floor as it snapped a three-game losing streak and won for the eighth straight time over Texas State (7-9, 2-1 SLC). With the Lions' top three scorers -- Daryl Cohen, Quennell Green and Terry Bryant -- held to a combined 15 points, Kevyn Green picked up the slack for Southeastern with his biggest game since scoring 15 in his Nov. 10 debut against Cal Poly. The nephew of former NBA great A.C. Green went 3-for-5 from behind the 3-point arc and 7-for-10 from the free throw line as Southeastern outscored Texas State, 41-33, in the second half. His 3-pointer with 17:25 remaining in the game capped a 5-0 run that gave Southeastern a 42-41 lead before adding a second trey two possessions later that put the Lions ahead, 47-43. Texas State answered with four straight points by Brandon Bush, who finished with a game-high 23 points, to tie the game at 47-47 before knotting the score at 49-49 on a layup with 12:43 left. But Sullivan, who went 7-for-7 from the floor and finished with 14 points and four blocks, gave Southeastern the lead for good on a dunk before Cohen hit a 3-pointer to extend the Lions' lead to 54-49 with 11:11 left. A jumper by Bush with 8:07 remaining in the first half gave Texas State its first lead of the game, 23-22, before both teams traded the lead six times before a basket by Kevyn Green tied the game at 37-37 at halftime. Brent Holder added 10 points for Texas State, which fell to 0-7 on the road and was held to its lowest scoring output since a 108-60 loss at UTEP on Dec. 19.
